records.addlTxt:
Defendant Matthew G Lutz in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to counts #2 and 3.  Court finds the defendant guilty of counts 2 and 3.  Count #1 is dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Defendants mother (victim) makes statements.  Attorney Fragoso makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  

The Court Orders the Following: Count # 2 
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
60 Days Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 3 days).  Concurrent to count #3.  
Term of Probation: 1 Year
Conditions of Probation:
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal contolled substances;
Sign any / all Medical Release for Agent;
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge
Anger management  counseling to be determined by Agent.  
COSTS:  $343.00 
DNA Surcharge: $200.00 
Bail to be applied from case # 15CF449 and 15CF587, the remainder of the money owed to be paid as a condition of probation.  
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.

